article.headline: Texas A&M 79, Washington 65
article.story:
COLLEGE STATION, Texas (AP) -- Takia Starks scored 25 points and
Morenike Atunrase had 21 as Texas A&M beat Washington 79-65 on
Sunday.

Starks scored 14 of her points in the first half, when Texas A&M
(3-2) rallied from a 13-point deficit and later outscored the
Huskies 47-15 during a 15-minute stretch.

Andrea Plouffe and Kayla Burt scored 13 points to lead
Washington (5-2), which shot 32 percent from the field in the
second half. Texas A&M scored 29 points off 20 turnovers by
Washington.

Katy Pounds had 11 points, nine rebound and nine assists off the
bench for the Aggies.
